git init: initialises a git repo
git config <--list|-l>: lists git config
git config --global user.name: returns username
git config --global user.email: returns email
git status: returns current status of all the files
git add <--a|.|filename>: adds files to staging area
git commit -m "Initial commit": commits the changes added to the staging area
git log: returns a log of all the commits

git clone <URL> [dirname]: clones a remote repo

.gitignore: git ignore files and patterns listed in this file

git diff [filename]: compares working directory with staging area
git diff --staged [filename]: compares last commit with statging area

git rm <filename>: removes a file and stages it
git mv <filename>: moves a file and stages it
git rm --cached <filename>: stops tracking filename

git log -p: shows the actual changes also
git log -p -n: shows last n logs
git log --stat: show short summary of the commits
other options:
  - git log --since=2.days
  - git log --pretty=<oneline|short|full>
  - git -log --format <format>
  - check git-log documentation
git commit --amend: change the current commit message

git restore --staged <filename>: unstages filename
git checkout -- <filename>: unmodifies staged and non-commited filename
git checkout -f: matches working directory with last commit

git remote add origin <URL>: creates an instance of a remote repo
git remote: returns the name of the url
git remote -v: push/pull url    
git push origin master: to push changes to github

git config --global <alias.aliasname commandname>: to alias commandname with aliasname

git checkout -b <branchname>: creates and switches to branchname
git merge branchname: mergers current branch with branchname

git branch: shows branch name
git branch <branchname>: changes branch to branchname
git branch -d <branchname>: to delete branch
git branch -v: show summary
git branch --merged: shows merged branched
git push origin --delete <branchname>: to delete branch from remote
git checkout <branchname>: changes to branchname


